<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 9:14AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...SNOW THROUGH THE MORNING...
Snow will continue until noontime before diminishing to snow
showers and flurries for the afternoon across the Capital Region,
Lake George Saratoga Region, northern and central Taconics,
Berkshires and southern Vermont. Visibitilies will lower to a half
mile at times. Additional snowfall will range from a quarter of an
inch to an inch with locally higher amounts up to two inches
especially over the higher terrain.</description>
